  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, Twitter data can be pre-processed before analysis, which is an essential aspect and supports exploratory analysis principles [67,68].Ethical considerations arise when scraping data from Twitter for analysis.",
    "A significant ethical concern is that while tweets are public by default, users do not provide their Twitter data explicitly for research purposes, making it practically unfeasible to obtain explicit consent for its use in research [69].",
    "We adhered to best practices recommended in social media research literature, ensuring that no identifiable tweets were included without prior consent from the tweet authors [70,71].",
    "This meant that tweets have been paraphrased in order to mitigate identification issues [72].",
    "The tweets were anonymised during the data cleaning process."
